Comment: The adoption of the new Law on Nature protection addressed the early existing legal gap of not having a delegated authority for marine protected areas. By the Law provision, responsible authority for the marine protected areas management is a Public enterprise Morsko Dobro. Local municipalities are responsible for proclamation.  The work on preparation of a protection study for the Platamuni area have been finalized in cooperation with the Agency for Environmental Protection. The final zoning of the marine part of the protected area was finalized as well.

The final study was delivered to Municipality of Kotor and local representatives will decide whether to undertake the proclamation process.

